{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Pass into Law rules on the length of Proroging Parliament.",
        "additional_details": "The Rules may be along these lines :-\r\n1. Standard Proroging of Parliment is always 5 days only.\r\n2. 66% of MP's vote needed to extend beyond 5 days i.e. a non-standard Proroging.\r\n3. only 1 Proroging allowed per 6 months, again with a 66% MP vote to overturn this rule.\r\n4. PM can call a Standard Proguing at any time within the rules.",
        "background": "Proroging should never again be used as a political  weapon to avoid parliamentary scrutiny.\r\nPassing Proroging rules into Law will have this effect.",
